The paper discusses deep learning approaches for question answering on knowledge bases, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of several sub-fields in computer science. Given that the paper focuses on natural language processing and machine learning techniques, it is likely to belong to the cs.CL (Computation and Language) sub-category. Additionally, since the paper evaluates different architectural design choices for deep learning models, it could also be classified under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also deals with information retrieval and database systems, which suggests that it could belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.DB (Databases) sub-categories.
